  "additional_note": "Some letters are \"non-connectors\" meaning they do not connect to the letter immediately following them. For these letters (Alif, Daal, Ḍaal, Zaal, Ray, Ṙay, Zey, Zhey, Wao), the initial, medial, and final forms often look the same as their isolated form when they are not connecting to the following letter. However, their connection to the preceding letter will change their appearance (e.g., ـد vs د). The table provides the most common representation for each form. For a more comprehensive learning experience, including how letters combine and specific word examples, you may want to explore the resources linked in the search results, particularly those offering video tutorials."
